{{Spanish name|Arango|Vega}}

'''Mar<U+00ED>a Cristina Arango Vega''' is the widow of the [[List of Presidents of Colombia|31st]] [[President of Colombia]], [[Misael Pastrana Borrero]], and served as [[First Lady of Colombia]] from 1970 to 1974. She is the mother of the 38th President [[Andr<U+00E9>s Pastrana Arango]].

==Personal life==
Mar<U+00ED>a Cristina was born in Bogot<U+00E1> to Carlos Arango V<U+00E9>lez, a [[Colombian Liberal Party|Liberal party]] politician, and his wife Mar<U+00ED>a Vega Jaramillo.<ref>{{cite journal|last=R<U+00ED>os Pe<U+00F1>aloza|first=Gilma|title=Primeras Damas del Siglo XX|journal=Credencial Historia|date=1996-08-01|issue=80|accessdate=4 November 2012|trans_title=First Ladies of the 20th Century|publisher=[[Bank of the Republic (Colombia){{!}}Colombia, Bank of the Republic]]|location=Bogot<U+00E1>|language=Spanish|issn=0121-3296|oclc=39236834 |url=http://old.lablaa.org/blaavirtual/revistas/credencial/agosto1996/agosto2.htm}}</ref>

In 1950, while her father was serving as Ambassador of Colombia to the [[Holy See]], she met [[Misael Pastrana Borrero]], who was working as a diplomat attached to her father's Embassy.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Pastrana Borrero, Misael|journal=Current Biography Yearbook|year=1972|volume=32|accessdate=3 November 2012|page=316|publisher=[[H. W. Wilson Company]]|location=The Bronx|issn=0084-9499|oclc=1565606 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=bZQYAAAAIAAJ}}</ref> They got engaged that year and married on 24 Febraury at the Saint Bartholomew School's Madonna Della Strada Chapel in Bogot<U+00E1>.<ref>{{cite book|last=<U+00C1>gredo Tobar|first=Reinaldo|title=Notas Biogr<U+00E1>ficas y Geneal<U+00F3>gicas|location=Bogot<U+00E1>|url=http://www.docstoc.com/docs/114185078/Santa-Fe-de-Bogot%EF%BF%BD-Junio-21-de-1999|accessdate=4 November 2012|page=14|language=Spanish|date=2007-12-27}}</ref> Together they had four children, Juan Carlos, [[Andr<U+00E9>s Pastrana Arango|Andr<U+00E9>s]], Jaime, and Mar<U+00ED>a Cristina.

